Facilities

Swarnandhra College of Engineering Technology (SCET) offers various facilities to its students. These facilities are designed to provide a conducive learning environment, support academic and extracurricular activities, and promote overall student well-being.

Infrastructure

The college has a sprawling campus with modern infrastructure, including state-of-the-art classrooms, laboratories, and workshops. has a well-planned and modern infrastructure that provides an ideal environment for learning and growth. The college has invested heavily in creating state-of-the-art facilities that cater to the needs of its students, faculty, and staff. The campus is equipped with a 155 Mbps bandwidth internet connection, enabling high-speed access. The college has a canteen within the campus catering to the needs of the students and staff.

classrooms

The college has spacious, well-ventilated, and air-conditioned classrooms equipped with modern teaching aids like LCD projectors, audio-visual systems, and smart boards. Swarnandhra College of Engineering Technology (SCET) has modern and well-equipped classrooms that provide an ideal learning environment for its students. The classrooms are designed to facilitate interactive learning, with a focus on student-centric education.

Spacious and Well-Ventilated: The classrooms are spacious, well-ventilated, and air-conditioned, providing a comfortable learning environment.
Modern Teaching Aids: The classrooms are equipped with modern teaching aids like LCD projectors, audio-visual systems, and smart boards.
Ergonomic Furniture: The classrooms have ergonomic furniture, including comfortable seating and desks, to promote student comfort and engagement.
Internet Connectivity: The classrooms have internet connectivity, enabling students to access online resources and learning platforms.

Library

The library at Swarnandhra College of Engineering and Technology is a central hub for academic and research activities. It is a well-equipped, modern library that provides access to a vast collection of books, journals, and digital resources. A variety of resources are available at the Swarnandhra College library to help faculty and students with their academic and research needs. Among the noteworthy establishments.

A variety of resources are available at the Swarnandhra College library to help faculty and students with their academic and research needs. Among the noteworthy establishments are:

Digital Library: The library offers databases, e-books, and online journals through its twenty-system digital library.
E-Journals: A number of e-journals, such as IEEE, Springer Nature, J-Gate, N-LIST, and DELNET, are available for subscription at the library.
Book Bank: SC students can use the library's book bank service.
Open Access Policy: The library has an open access policy that permits patrons to wander around the stock area at will.
Online Public Access Catalogue (OPAC): Users can search and access books and other resources online thanks to the library's OPAC system.

ATM

Swarnandhra College of Engineering and Technology has an ATM facility available on its campus, with ATMs from State Bank of India (SBI) and Andhra Bank. This facility is available 24/7 for the convenience of students. Additionally , the college has a tie-up with Andhra Bank to provide education loans to students. Outers also use this ATM to debit money.

Mess

Swarnandhra College of Engineering and Technology has a mess facility available for hostelrs and its students. The mess facility provides hygienic and nutritious food to the students. The college has a separate mess committee that looks after the mess facility and ensures that the food is prepared and served in a clean and hygienic environment. The mess committee also takes care of the menu and ensures that the food is varied and nutritious. The mess facility is available for both boys and girls and provides breakfast, lunch, and dinner. The college also has a canteen that provides snacks and other food items to the students.
